 The Nigerian Institute of Quantity Surveyors (NIQS) Foundation is determined to address challenges of climate change, social housing, gender equality, among others. The Chairman of the Board of Trustees of the foundation, Mr Segun Ajanlekoko, who made this known during a courtesy call on the President of NIQS, Mr Olayemi Shonubi, said the foundation was the vehicle through which the noble profession of quantity surveying could impact the world positively. Ajanlekoko, who is a past president of the foundation, said the profession was an endangered one, but assured that through the positive impact of the foundation on humanity, the nobility of the profession would be brought back to limelight.